<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 15 at 6:46AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Band of snow and falling temperatures this morning...
A band of moderate to locally heavy snow will move across the area
this morning. While precipitation may briefly start out as rain in
some of the still warm valleys, expect a quick changeover to snow.
This quick changeover to snow, along with temperatures initially
above freezing, could cause for some slushy and icy conditions
for your morning commute. Ensure ample time to arrive to your
destination this morning and be prepared for changing road
conditions.</description>
